(292, 3, 'International treaties have mandated that freshwater pollution receive equal research funding as oceanic pollution.'),
(292, 4, 'They adsorb toxic substances, accumulate through the food chain, and may pose risks to human health that surpass those of ocean pollution.'),

(293, 1, 'Governments have taken only limited steps, partly because the lack of standardized data makes it difficult to develop comprehensive regulations.'),
(293, 2, 'Most governments have implemented sweeping bans on all single-use plastics in response to the freshwater crisis.'),
(293, 3, 'Governments have prioritized freshwater microplastic regulation over oceanic pollution controls.'),
(293, 4, 'International cooperation has resulted in enforceable global standards for microplastic contamination levels.'),

(294, 1, 'the economic costs of microplastic remediation will eventually exceed the total value of the global fishing industry'),
(294, 2, 'many freshwater ecosystems are approaching irreversible tipping points beyond which ecological recovery may no longer be feasible'),
(294, 3, 'microplastic contamination in freshwater is entirely a consequence of inadequate wastewater treatment infrastructure'),
(294, 4, 'the only viable solution is a complete global ban on all synthetic polymer production within the next decade');

